$interpreted: Ned: Lisa, what's the matter?
Lisa: D, do you still have the Rainbow Roses?
Ned: Of course I do. It has only been 10 days.
Lisa: I'm here to inform you. Father has found three nasty-looking folks and asked them to take the Rainbow Roses from you.

Ned: Another one of Sir Sherlock's trials?
No need to worry; I'll deal with them as usual.
Lisa: No good. They are different from the previous thugs; I can feel that they are much more capable. It won't be easy to deal with them.
Ned: What? What kind of people are they?
Lisa: A Queen Kong with a bow and arrow, shady Red Riding Hood...
Lisa: Oh, and a handsome fellow who's half-naked~
Ned: Huh? A handsome what?
Lisa: Not important. All in all, I already have a strategy in mind.
Ned: Rainbow Roses!?
Lisa: A counterfeit, of course~ after the incident last time, I set up some prevention methods to prevent father from messing with our business again.
Lisa: When those folks come, you will pretend to be defeated and allow them to take these fake Rainbow Roses.
Lisa: By doing so, father will think that his scheme has succeeded and won't bother screwing with us until the wedding is over~
Ned: Understood. I would have never thought of this. Lisa, you are so smart!
Lisa: Aww, you don't have to flatter me~ All things considered, follow my instructions. Remember to act naturally!
Ned: No problem. It's just acting. I can handle it just fine!
Lisa: Good. Then I'll have you take care of the rest~
Ned: So they're here!
Nigel: Northeast hunting grounds... is this it?
Naya: Shoot! Wasted so much time......
Angelia: Hmm. Will Ned really have the Rainbow Roses?
Ned: Um...

Ned: Ahaha~ Ladies and gentlemen,
I am the notorious Ned... And you bunch...
Ned: Ahem... after the Rainbow Roses, are ya?
Angelia: Spilling the beans, just like that?!

Naya: Now that we've gone over the formalities...
Hand them over!
Ned: Catch me if you can... hehe... if you dare!
Nigel: This lizard darts pretty fast...
Ned: That should do?
Ned: Ohhhhh~ Nooooooo~
Angelia: Man down yet?!

Ned: Beginner's luck... I give up...
I do have the Rainbow Roses.
Ned: Underneath the left side of my belt.
Nigel: ……….
Angelia: Ooh la la~ What exquisite petals!
Naya: Those are the Rainbow Roses?
Naya: Right, we have unfinished business to tend to!
Nigel: Don't you feel it?... Something doesn't add up...
Naya: Whatever. We found our fancy flowers, let's go!
Ned: How did it go? Did we succeed?
Lisa: We did indeed succeed... but Ned, your acting was kinda... horrendous, don't you think?
Ned: Is that so...

Lisa: I guess that's fine too.
I won't have to worry about you cheating and lying to me~
Ned: Umm, what does that have to do with me being a bad actor?

Lisa: No big deal, let's get moving.
Did you get injured? Do you need to see a doctor?
